Definition.WordDefinition: Jellyfish \Jel"ly*fish`\, n. (Zo["o]l.) Any one of the acalephs, esp. one of the larger species, having a jellylike appearance. See {Medusa} and {acaleph}. [1913 Webster]

jellyfish n 1: large siphonophore having a bladderlike float and stinging tentacles [syn: {Portuguese man-of-war}, {man-of-war}] 2: any of numerous usually marine and free-swimming coelenterates that constitute the sexually reproductive forms of hydrozoans and scyphozoans [syn: {medusa}, {medusan}] [also: {jellyfishes} (pl)]
